mercury-qt (0.2.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Allow setting host and port via the GUI.
  * Auto-negotiate WSS/WS on connection failure.
  * Only apply SSL config on wss:// connections.
  * Handle 'none' radio type from backend.
  * Include MSVC runtime DLLs in Windows bundle.
  * Use versioned directory name in Windows bundle zip.

 -- Rafael Diniz <rafael@rhizomatica.org>  Sat, 29 Mar 2026 12:00:00 +0000

mercury-qt (0.2.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Replace UDP client with QWebSocket client (supports JSON + binary spectrum frames).
  * Use backend-provided audio/radio lists and send combined commands over WebSocket.
  * Adjusted waterfall rendering order.
  * Update Wine bundle run helper.

 -- Rafael Diniz <rafael@rhizomatica.org>  Tue, 18 Mar 2026 12:18:00 +0000

mercury-qt (0.1.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add Debian packaging metadata for mercury-qt.
  * Ship the renamed launcher wrapper so debhelper can stage the package cleanly.
  * Depend on the Mercury backend and python3-numpy at runtime.
  * Document the Wine-hosted Windows bundle workflow.

 -- Rafael Diniz <rafael@rhizomatica.org>  Tue, 10 Mar 2026 21:05:27 +0000
